channel.description:
Hello,

I am using Frontity for about a week now and I am already excited. However, building a new website I found a topic that is not very well documented (at least for me). I am using [WP REST API Sidebars](https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-rest-api-sidebars/) plugin to expose widgets in the REST API, however as the plugin creates a custom endpoint, I am not sure how to access this endpoint and get the info.

For example, for a CPT I am using the following code in my theme's index.js file:

    actions: {
        theme: {
          beforeSSR: async ({ actions }) => {
            await actions.source.fetch('/my-cpt/');
          }
        }

How can I get the info from a custom endpoint? Is there any example in the documentation I missed?

Thanks in advance.
